main event: On September 20, 1963, a witness reported observing an unidentified flying object off the coast of Arcata, California, which exhibited movement up and down and then disappeared.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 1 minute and 45 seconds., The object was noted as unidentifiable with no known aircraft matching its description., The report indicated that there was no radar return for the object., The case requires more detailed information to determine the object's nature., Previous sightings in the area had raised interest in similar unusual activity.
